==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chasseur
<hw>Chas`seur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a huntsman.
See <er>Chase</er> to pursue.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>One of a body of light troops, cavalry or infantry, trained for
rapid movements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An attendant upon persons of rank or wealth, wearing
a plume and sword.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great <qex>chasseur</qex> who had announced her arrival.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chassis</ent>⟦br⟧
